[01:41.15]Prince Michael sat on his favourite bench and smiled.  It was a diverting thought to him that he was wealthy enough to buy every one of those close-ranged, bulky, window-lit mansions that faced him, if he chose.  He could have matched gold, equipages, jewels, art treasures, estates and acres with any Croesus in this proud city of Manhattan, and scarcely have entered upon the bulk of his holdings. 
迈克尔王子坐在他最爱的长椅上笑了起来。想来有趣，如果他愿意的话，他有足够的钱买下面前任何一幢结构紧凑、气势宏伟、窗明几净的宅邸。
他拥有的黄金、马车、珠宝、艺术珍品、庄园和地产足以和纽约这座尊贵之城里的任何一个富豪相媲美。

