[03:01.29]These thoughts strayed dreamily through the mind of Prince Michael, as he smiled under the stubble of his polychromatic beard.  Lounging thus, clad as the poorest of mendicants in the parks, he loved to study humanity.  He found in altruism（利他主义） more pleasure than his riches, his station and all the grosser sweets of life had given him. 
